# Line-ending normalization.
#
# The repo is LF. Windows editors — notably Obsidian, which re-saves notes with
# CRLF the moment they're opened — otherwise leave files showing as phantom
# "modified" with no content change. This file is authoritative for EOL (it
# overrides core.autocrlf, and ships to every clone + CI). Locally it's paired
# with `git config core.autocrlf false` so git doesn't double-handle EOL.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply text/EOL conversion.
*.glb binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.webp binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
